<!DOCTYPE html>
<!-- =========================================================================
  Helix Proxy — branded Squid error page for deny_info 503:ERR_TUNNEL_DOWN
  Served when the external_acl helper returns ERR (tunnel down / Redis stale /
  no route). This is the FAIL-CLOSED user-facing signal: the request was NOT
  sent out directly (no VPN leak) and Squid stays alive (PID unchanged).
  Deployment: copy this file into Squid's active error directory (the dir
  referenced by `error_directory`, or the per-language default e.g.
  /usr/share/squid/errors/en/) so `deny_info 503:ERR_TUNNEL_DOWN` resolves it.
  Squid macros used: %U (request URL), %T (local time). DESIGN / template.
============================================================================ -->
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>503 — VPN tunnel unavailable</title>
  <style>
    :root { color-scheme: light dark; }
    body { margin: 0; font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, "Segoe UI", Roboto, sans-serif;
           background: #0f1115; color: #e6e8ec; display: flex; min-height: 100vh;
           align-items: center; justify-content: center; }
    .card { max-width: 32rem; padding: 2.5rem; margin: 1rem; border-radius: 14px;
            background: #171a21; box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.35);
            border: 1px solid #232733; }
    .badge { display: inline-block; font-size: .72rem; letter-spacing: .12em;
             text-transform: uppercase; color: #ffb454; border: 1px solid #ffb454;
             border-radius: 999px; padding: .2rem .6rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
    h1 { font-size: 1.45rem; margin: 0 0 .6rem; }
    p  { line-height: 1.55; margin: .5rem 0; color: #b9bec9; }
    .spin { display: inline-block; width: .9rem; height: .9rem; margin-right: .45rem;
            border: 2px solid #ffb454; border-top-color: transparent; border-radius: 50%;
            vertical-align: -1px; animation: r .9s linear infinite; }
    @keyframes r { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }
    .meta { margin-top: 1.5rem; font-size: .8rem; color: #6b7280;
            border-top: 1px solid #232733; padding-top: 1rem; word-break: break-all; }
    code { color: #9ecbff; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <main class="card">
    <span class="badge">Helix Proxy · 503</span>
    <h1>The VPN tunnel for this request is unavailable</h1>
    <p><span class="spin" aria-hidden="true"></span><strong>Retrying automatically.</strong>
       Your request was <strong>not</strong> sent over an unprotected connection — the
       proxy fails closed to keep your traffic private.</p>
    <p>This is temporary. As soon as the tunnel's health check reports it back up,
       the next request will go through with no action needed on your side. You may
       simply reload in a few seconds.</p>
    <div class="meta">
      Requested resource: <code>%U</code><br>
      Time: %T<br>
      Reference: <code>ERR_TUNNEL_DOWN</code>
    </div>
  </main>
</body>
</html>
